.TH LOGICD 8 "@HIDLOOM_VERSION@" "HIDloom" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
logicd \- keyboard logic companion daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 -m logicd.logicd
[\fICONFIG_JSON\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B logicd
owns high-level keymap, layer, control socket, notification, and companion
integration behavior. In the native-owner configuration, hidloom-logicd-core owns
the hot matrix input path and logicd runs as the companion service.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Common variables include \fBLOG_LEVEL\fR, \fBLOGICD_LED_STATE_PATH\fR,
\fBLOGICD_CORE_KEY_EVENT_CTRL_SOCKET\fR, \fBLOGICD_MATRIX_ROWS\fR, and
\fBLOGICD_MATRIX_COLS\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hidloom-logicd-core (8),
.BR matrixd (8),
.BR hidloom-ctrl (1),
.BR hidloom-keymap (5)
.br
Daemon documentation:
https://github.com/cqa02303/hidloom/tree/@HIDLOOM_GIT_SHA@/docs/daemon
